noun.description: The action or process of filing something for a second or subsequent time; an instance of this.

origin: Mid 19th century; earliest use found in Circular Orders Court of Sudder Dewanny Adawlut. Probably partly from refile + -ing, and partly from re- + filing<br>late 19th century; earliest use found in Horace Greeley (1811–1872). Either from re- + filing, or from refile + -ing.
